Description: Multi-WAN firewall, DHCP server, VPN and router (full appliance)
 NetFirewall is an opinionated home/SOHO firewall stack built from scratch on
 .NET 10 + PostgreSQL. It bundles a hardened privileged daemon, a web UI, a
 DHCP server, a WAN failover monitor, and a console TUI for offline / break
 -glass administration.
 .
 This package installs:
   * /opt/netfirewall/{daemon,web,tui,migrations} — published binaries
   * /etc/netfirewall/{daemon,web}.env — secrets (mode 0600 / 0640)
   * Two systemd units: netfirewall-daemon, netfirewall-web
   * /usr/local/bin/netfirewall-tui symlink + manpage + bash completion
 .
 The post-install script provisions the `netfirewall` system group, the
 `netfirewall-web` service user, generates an AES-256 master key (used by
 the daemon to encrypt TOTP secrets at rest), and runs database migrations
 against the configured PostgreSQL instance.
 .
 First-time configuration via the web UI requires a bootstrap token, printed
 to journalctl on the first start with an empty users table. See
 /usr/share/doc/netfirewall/README.Debian for the unattended-install path.
